concept.title: POLYSOLID Command
concept.shortdesc: Creates a 3D solid in the shape of a wide, extruded polyline.

conbody.p: Create a 3D solid in the shape of a wide, extruded polyline with multiple line and arc segments. Options allow you to specify the width, height and justification.

section.title: Methods to create a polysolid
section.p: There are two methods to begin creating a polysolid:

section.title: Additional options within the POLYSOLID command
section.p: After you begin creating a polysolid, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Specify the height of the polysolid.
The height is saved in the PSOLHEIGHT.
Specify the width of the polysolid.
The width is saved in the .

Specify the position of the polysolid with respect to the base path.
Left: The left edge of the polysolid follows the base path.
Right: The right edge of the polysolid follows the base path.
Center: The center of the polysolid follows the base path.
When Hot Key Assistant (HKA) is enabled, the following widget allows you to dynamically switch between left, center, and right justification by pressing the Ctrl key.

Specify whether polysolid creates an individual 3D solid for each segment or a single 3D solid for all the segments.
On: Create individual solids.
Off: Create a single solid.

Specify whether you are prompted to specify the height when creating a polysolid.
On: You are prompted to specify the height.
